The paper deals with image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for this task suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the difficulties encountered by classical registration approaches, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The application of the proposed method to remote sensing further suggests that it may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
